Class AbstractManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread
      • net.ssehub.comani.core.AbstractManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AnalysisManager, ExtractionManager
    public abstract class AbstractManager
extends java.lang.Thread
    This abstract class defines common methods and elements of the specific commit extraction and analysis managers.
    Author:
    Christian Kroeher

    • Field Detail

      • logger

        protected Logger logger
        The logger for displaying messages on the console.

      • operatingSystem

        protected java.lang.String operatingSystem
        The name of the operating system on which the tool is currently executed.

      • versionControlSystem

        protected java.lang.String versionControlSystem
        The name of the version control system from which the commits are extracted.

      • plugInClassName

        protected java.lang.String plugInClassName
        The fully-qualified class name of the desired extractor or analyzer (plug-in). The default value is null, which should be changed by the specific managers based on their respective properties.

      • properties

        protected java.util.Properties properties
        The properties determining the extraction or analysis process, e.g., the fully-qualified class name of the respective plug-ins to use, or the path to the directory, in which extracted commits and analysis results shall be saved. This properties object contains all properties defined in the properties file, which start with the prefix:
        • "extraction." for extraction properties and
        • "analysis." for analysis properties
        Extraction properties will not be available for analyses and vice-versa.

      • commitQueue

        protected CommitQueue commitQueue
        The CommitQueue for transferring commits from an extractor to an analyzer.

      • outputDirectory

        protected java.lang.String outputDirectory
        The string defining the output directory in which extracted commits or analysis results will be saved. The default value is null, which should avoid saving commits or results to a file. This is changed in accordance to the respective properties if they are defined.

      • isReady

        protected boolean isReady
        The flag for indicating whether this manager is ready to run() (true) or not (false). If its values is false run() will do nothing. Execute isReady to change the flag value.

      • isReady

        protected boolean isReady()
        Returns whether this manager is ready to run() (true) or not (false). If the values is false run() will do nothing. Executing this method will change the value if setting up and configuring the manager was successful.
        Returns:
        true if this manager is ready for execution; false otherwise

        protected abstract boolean go()
        Starts the extraction or analysis process using the properties given during construction of this object. Note that method is only called if setup() returned true.
        Returns:
        true if the extraction or analysis process was successful; false otherwise
